t managers including pimco bonds rcm equities and degi real estate allianz sold dresdner bank to commerzbank in november  as a result of this transaction allianz gained a  controlling stake in the new commerzbank contents  history  foundation  th century developments  st century developments  operations  australia  belgium  bulgaria  canada  colombia  germany  india  indonesia  italy  malaysia  pakistan  slovakia  united kingdom  united states  senior management  ceos to date  sponsorships  naziera activities and litigation  see also  references  external links historyedit foundationedit an early allianz agents plaque allianz ag was founded in berlin on  february  by then director of the munich reinsurance company carl von thieme a native of erfurt whose father was the director of thuringia and wilhelm von finck coowner of the merck finck  co bank the joint company was listed in berlins trade register under the name allianz versicherungsaktiengesellschaft the first allianz products were marine and accident policies first sold only in germany however in  allianz opened its first international branch office in london it distributed marine insurance coverage to german clientele looking for coverage abroad in  the company became the first insurer to obtain a license to distribute corporate policies in  paul von naher took over the sole leadership of the company as it moved into the us and other markets markets entered by  included the netherlands italy belgium france the scandinavian countries and the baltic states and allianz had become the largest maritime insurer in germany the company suffered an early disaster in expansion when the  san francisco earthquake caused the company to sustain  marks in losses in  the company acquired fides insurance company a firm that had innovated the first form of home invasion insurance other places it would expand into during the s and s included palestine cyprus iraq china the dutch indies ceylon and siam th century developmentsedit in  the company began to offer fire insurance and in  it began to sell machinery breakdown policies allianz remained the only company in the world that sold machine breakdown insurance until  then in  it began to offer automobile insurance as well in  von naher died and was succeeded by kurt schmitt the company would begin to offer life insurance as of  becoming europes largest offerer of the policies by the end of the s in  allianz merged with stuttgarter verein versicherung ag and  two years later acquired the insurance businesses of favag a large german insurer that declared bankruptcy due to the onset of the great depression expansion of the company then slowed until  at which point it employed more than  people christian stadler wrote of the history of allianz that it shows how important it is to diversify into related areas to hedge against the risk of fundamental changes in markets and economies during world war ii the berlin headquarters of allianz were destroyed by allied bombing runs following the end of the war in  hans heß became head of the company and allianz shifted its headquarters to munich in  due to the split between east and west germany heß only held the position until  when he was replaced by hans goudefroy after world war ii global business activities were gradually resumed allianz opened an office in paris in  and started repurchasing stakes in former subsidiaries in italy and austria in  wolfgang schieren became the head of the company these expansions were followed in the s by the establishment of business in the united kingdom the netherlands spain brazil and the united states in  allianz acquired cornhill insurance plc london and the purchase of a stake in riunione adriatica di sicurità ras milan strengthened its presence in western and southern europe in the s in  allianz started an expansion into eight eastern european countries with establishing a presence in hungary in the same decade allianz also acquired firemans fund an insurer in the united states which was followed by the purchase of assurances générales de france agf paris these acquisitions were followed by the expansion into asia with several joint ventures and acquisitions in china and south korea and the acquisition of australias manufacturers mutual insurance around this time allianz expanded its asset management business as well by purchasing for example asset management companies in california st century developmentsedit the original allianz logo designed in  by karl schulpig allianzs current head office is located in munich in april  allianz agreed to acquire the  per cent of dresdner bank that it did not already own for us billion as part of the transaction allianz agreed to sell its  per cent stake in hypovereinsbank to munich re and to acquire munich res  per cent stake in allianz leben following completion of the acquisition allianz and dresdner bank combined their asset management activities by forming allianz global investors in  michael diekmann succeeded henning schultenoelle as ceo of allianz ag in june  allianz announced the layoff of  employees about  percent of its worldwide work force at the time as part of a restructuring program aimed at raising profitability the reductions comprised  staff at allianz insurance operations and  at dresdner bank in the same month allianz announced that its dresdner kleinwort wasserstein investment banking operation would be renamed as simply dresdner kleinwort in september  allianz announced that it would convert its holding company into a societas europaea se latin european company becoming one of the first major companies to do so the conversion was made in conjunction with allianzs acquisition of  per cent control of its principal italian subsidiary riunione adriatica di sicurtà ras for around us billion the conversion to an se was completed on  october  the allianz group also simplified its brand strategy from  and their previous emblem was replaced by the current combination mark by  the company was europes largest insurer in  it was a founder member of the hedge fund standards board which sets a voluntary code of standards of best practice endorsed by its members on  august  it was announced that allianz had agreed to sell  per cent of dresdner bank to commerzbank for € billion us billion with an agreement that commerzbank would acquire the remainder of dresdner bank by the end of  after renegotiations it was announced in november  that commerzbank would acquire the  ownership of dresdner bank earlier  january  the sale price was lowered to  billion euro shortly after the transaction completed commerzbank was partially nationalized by the german government to save it from bankruptcy allianz currently retains a stake of around  in commerzbank in august  a consortium led by allianz acquired german motorway service station group tankrast for an undisclosed sum believed to be in the region of € billion operationsedit allianz has operations in over  countries and has around  employees the parent company allianz se is headquartered in munich germany allianz has more than  million customers worldwide and its services include property and casualty insurance life and health insurance and asset management in  it was number  on the global forbes  list countries in which allianz currently has operations australiaedit tracing its roots back to  allianz australia insurance limited operates throughout australia and new zealand and through its subsidiaries offers a range of insurance and risk management products and services subsidiaries of allianz australia include club marine allianz life and hunter premium funding in  allianz australia announced a multiyear agreement with the scg trust to rename the sydney football stadium to allianz stadium allianz ag is the underwriter for australias largest pet insurance company petplan australia belgiumedit allianz operates through allianz belgium previously agf belgium which has been rebranded to allianz belgium 